12 Sec. 2. NEW SECTION. 279.87 Limitation on the use of
13 personal electronic devices.
14 1. Commencing with the school year beginning July 1, 2025,
15 the board of directors of each school district shall adopt
16 policies regarding student use of personal electronic devices
17 during school hours that restrict student use of such devices
18 during classroom instructional time. The policies must meet
19 all of the following requirements:
20 a. Identify policies and information related to various
21 educational devices and technologies that will be made
22 available to students for instructional purposes.
23 b. Identify the methods that a parent or guardian of
24 a student may use to communicate with the student during
25 school hours or while the student is participating in a
26 school-sponsored activity.
27 c. Identify the methods that a parent or guardian of a
28 student may use to communicate with the student during an
29 emergency situation.
30 d. Include protocols that the school district will use to
31 securely store a student’s personal electronic device when such
32 device is in the possession of the school district.
33 e. Specify the discipline associated with a student’s
34 violation of the policies, including the discipline associated
35 with a student’s use of a personal electronic device during
